        }
      ],
      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">In an emergency department, a physician treats a patient with a severe bacterial infection. The physician notes that certain components of the patient&#39;s immune system are facilitating phagocytosis by marking the bacteria for easier identification and engulfment by phagocytes. Which of the following is acting as an opsonin in this scenario?</span></span></span></span></p>",
      "unique_key": "Q5929190",
